br>
<br>
Then, Innoruuk himself brought forth the very thing Zaith relied on for his power. Hate. All emotions, anger, fear, terror and frustration left him. Only a pure, red hot hate filled him. The paladins well timed spell held no effect on him then. The power of his Order filled him to his very core. Turning, Zaith took the needed steps twards Tunyric to place his gauntleted hand against the paladins armored back. His normal steel grey eyes flashed red. His voice boomed across the tavern</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
