<br>
She wanted so badly to rush out, fight with him if needed, but she was young. Too young to do anything to most here, Xiashya realized. No, she would just be a burden to her father if she went out into the open. She wanted to call out, to scream for him to stop. Whatever image of him that she held, the wisdom he imparted to her, the security he gave her... Xiashya wanted to hold on to that.<br>
<br>
Was it possible? It seemed like things were repaired just to be broken again... and again... and again.... It was Hate. It was Hate that always brought back the 'always' and 'again'. Maybe it had sent her Tunyric just to break her faith, but Xiashya would prove her worth to Lady Marr, even if it meant her last breath. She smiled, still cradling the fondness she had carried for her adoptive father since the day they had met. How could she turn her back on him, even after what she had seen?<br>
<br>
&quot;Never,&quot; she swore to herself in a whisper. &quot;Never, and it would shatter the 'always'.&quot; <p>Xiashya<br>
Bard of the 17th season<br>
