<br>
She looks up to see a young, female Bard in the shadows of the room. Her face is distraught and this tugs at Seraphimm's heart. Thier eyes meet for a moment, both of them care for people in this room and they are both well aware either, or all can die.<br>
<br>
Feeling Zaith shift his weight above her brings her back to the moment and her position. She looks over her shoulder up at him and she knows he is ready for her to move away. She scrambles from beneath him, though would rather stay under his protective frame. Quickly she stands turning to see Tunyric holding the point of a spear at her Commandant's throat.<br>
<br>
She stands in a firm stance, her eyes locked on those of Tunyric, &quot;Kill him if you will. The Lust will continue on. It has continued on without Gore. It has continued on without Tyriek. It will continue on without him. He knows this. He is aware he cannot be held ransom at the risk of the Lust.&quot; A slight grin creeps across her face as her soft, blue eyes turn a cold gray.<br>
